codex
I found a second classification bug while preparing the push: the feedback loop compares branches against the local `main`, not `origin/main`, so any stale local main makes review status wrong. I’m fixing that too and adding a regression test, because it directly affects whether this branch is actually merge-ready after push.
Plan update
Expanded the verification step because a second real defect surfaced: feedback-loop classification was comparing against stale local main instead of origin/main.
  ✓ Refactor coding_feedback_loop root/kanban discovery to be worktree-aware instead of hardcoded to the main workspace path
  ✓ Add regression coverage for default root discovery in tests.test_coding_feedback_loop
  → Prefer origin/main over stale local main in branch classification and cover it with a regression test
  • Run targeted verification, push feature branch to origin, and capture the resulting branch status
